members.name: DOMMatrixReadOnly.multiplySelf()
members.description: Returns itself, a DOMMatrix,  with its new content being the result of the original matrix being multiplied by the given DOMMatrix.

members.name: DOMMatrixReadOnly.preMultiplySelf()
members.description: Returns itself, a DOMMatrix,  with its new content being the result of the given DOMMatrix being multiplied by the original matrix.

members.name: DOMMatrix.translateSelf()
members.description: Returns itself, a DOMMatrix, with its new content being the result of the matrix being translated by the given vector.

members.name: DOMMatrix.scaleSelf()
members.description: Returns itself, a DOMMatrix, with its new content being the result of the matrix x and y dimensions being scaled by the given factor, centered on the origin given.

members.name: DOMMatrix.scale3dSelf()
members.description: Returns itself, a DOMMatrix, with its new content being the result of the matrix x, y and z dimension being scaled by the given factor, centered on the origin given.

members.name: DOMMatrix.scaleNonUniformSelf()
members.description: Returns itself, a DOMMatrix, with its new content being the result of the matrix x, y and z dimension being scaled by the given factor for each dimension, centered on the origin given.

members.name: DOMMatrix.rotateSelf()
members.description: Returns itself, a DOMMatrix, with its new content being the result of the original matrix being rotated by the given angle, with the rotation centered on the origin given.

members.name: DOMMatrix.rotateFromVectorSelf()
members.description: Returns itself, a DOMMatrix, with its new content being the result of the original matrix being rotated by the angle between the given vector and (1,0), centered on the origin given.

members.name: DOMMatrix.rotateAxisAngleSelf()
members.description: Returns itself, a DOMMatrix, with its new content being the result of the original matrix being rotated by the given angle and the give vector.

members.name: DOMMatrix.skewXSelf()
members.description: Returns itself, a DOMMatrix, with its new content being the result of the original matrix being skewed along the x-axis by the given factor.

members.name: DOMMatrix.skewYSelf()
members.description: Returns itself, a DOMMatrix, with its new content being the result of the original matrix being skewed along the y-axis by the given factor.

members.name: DOMMatrix.invertSelf()
members.description: Returns itself,  a DOMMatrix, with its new content being the result of the original matrix being inverted. If the matrix cannot be inverted, all its components are set to NaN and is2D() returns false.

members.name: DOMMatrix.setMatrixValue()
members.description: Returns itself, a DOMMatrix, with its describing the matrix representing the same transformation as the CSS transform functions given in parameter.
